Note: All images have sources added in the comments field of the respective files.

1. CS History Museum

A museum of computer science history, home to invaluable pieces of technology that pioneered the development of computers etc.

2. Immersive VR world

An live multiplayer VR experience, with complete interactive fantasy worlds to choose from.

3. Fractal Land

An exhibition of constantly evolving computer generated art using the recursive power of fractals, along with a fractal mirror
that generates the user's image using fractals.

4. Celebrity Machines/ Meet the Stars

A gallery where visitors can hang out with legendary machines from pop culture, including HAL 9000, R2D2, C3PO, Sonny, Wall-E etc.